# System Documentation & Changelog Management

## System Context

Multi-tenant QR Menu & Google Review SaaS (MenuHub):
- Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Prisma ORM, PostgreSQL
- NextAuth.js (`SUPERADMIN`, `TENANT` roles)
- Docker standalone build for Coolify
- **100% English only** across codebase, UI, logs, seeds, and docs

## Mandatory README Maintenance

After completing a task, feature, or config refactor, inspect root `README.md`. Update or keep complete:
- Functional architecture (Landing, Public Menu/Wi-Fi Gate, Tenant Dashboard, Super Admin, Cron Runner)
- Local setup with environment variable specifications
- Build and Docker standalone flags for production

## Incremental CHANGELOG Updates

Maintain root `CHANGELOG.md` using [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) format:
- Append or update on every file change, script, schema update, or structural UI change
- Group under dated sections: `### Added`, `### Changed`, `### Fixed`

## Pre-Finish Checklist

Before finishing any user request:
1. Did architecture change? Update relevant `README.md` sections.
2. Did code change? Log micro-changes under today's date in `CHANGELOG.md`.
